cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about training sequence-to-sequence models for natural language processing tasks such as machine translation and speech recognition. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper mentions speech synthesis as one of the tasks that can be solved using OpenSeq2Seq. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of mixed-precision training to improve the efficiency of training these models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper is about developing tools for building AI models. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions distributed training as a feature of OpenSeq2Seq, which could be relevant to systems and control applications.
